  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empowering smallholder farmers against disaster and emergency impacts in Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to ensure the preparedness of small scale farmers  for the impacts of disasters and emergencies in view of their vulnerability especially women, and limited capacity to recover from such impacts. The project will facilitate processes that will advocate and support relevant movements for policy reforms and the development of intruments to support SHF in the event of disasters and emergencies. The project also aims to build the adapative capacity of farmers to these, while reducing their economic losses from disasters and emergencies and facilitation of public support to them. The project supports SCO 1.1, 4, 5.1</narrative>
  </description>
